The paper discusses the development of an exemplar for model-based architectural self-adaptation, which falls under the domain of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the simulation of adaptable software, which could be related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the exploration of variants of adaptation engines, which could be related to programming languages (cs.PL) and deep learning (cs.DL).
